  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="KT249-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">varaiviṭai vaippa “āṟṟakiṟṟiyō” eṉṟa tōḻikkuk kiḻatti uraittatu. </p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Told by HER to the confidante who said “don't you have
          the strength?”, when the time of marriage had been fixed. </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="KT249">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l> iṉamayi lakavu marampayil kāṉattu</l>
          <l> naraimuka vūkam pārppoṭu paṉippap</l>
          <l> paṭumaḻai poḻinta cāra lavarnāṭṭuk</l>
          <l> kuṉṟa nōkkiṉeṉ ṟōḻi</l>
          <l> paṇṭai yaṟṟō kaṇṭici ṉutalē.</l>
        </lg>

        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
          <l>I looked, friend, at the hill</l>
          <l rend="indent3">of his land of slopes flooded with falling rain,</l>
          <l rend="indent2">so that the white-faced black monkey with [its] young one shivers</l>
          <l rend="indent">in the forest, where trees rustle <note place="foot">Or: "where in the
            forest dense with trees peacocks call out in groups."</note> [and] peacocks call out in
            groups.</l>
          <l>[Was] it like that before? Look, [my] forehead.</l>

          <lg type="alternate" sameAs="5b" resp="#TVG">
            <l>[Is] it [again] such as it [was] before? Look, [my] forehead. <note place="foot">Thus
              T.V.G. who thinks the point is that seeing his hill is a restorative for her beauty,
              nearly as much as seeing himself.</note>
            </l>
          </lg>

        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
